{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17584218","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17584218"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:42:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:42:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14432"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14432","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14432"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.44,0.07,0.02,0.47]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7127"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"60240"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7127","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7127"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14432"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"45660"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"40"},{"type":"tags","id":"41"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4903"},{"type":"tags","id":"4905"},{"type":"tags","id":"4910"},{"type":"tags","id":"4926"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"9855"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"17030"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17145"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"60240","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/60240"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following statements is correct regarding the bundle of His?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["It is the primary pacemaker of the heart","It can act as a pacemaker if the sinoatrial and atrioventricular nodes fail","It connects directly to the sinoatrial node","It has an intrinsic rhythm of 60-80 beats per minute","It receives pacing signals from the atrioventricular node"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe bundle of His is a crucial component of the cardiac conduction system. Here\u0027s why the correct answer is that \u003Cstrong\u003Eit can act as a pacemaker if the sinoatrial and atrioventricular nodes fail\u003C/strong\u003E:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe bundle of His is part of the heart\u0027s electrical conduction system, located between the atrioventricular node and the bundle branches. While it is not \u003Cstrong\u003Ethe primary pacemaker of the heart\u003C/strong\u003E (which is the sinoatrial node), it can indeed serve as a backup pacemaker if both the sinoatrial and atrioventricular nodes fail. In such cases, the bundle of His can generate electrical impulses at a rate of 40-60 beats per minute.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe bundle of His does not \u003Cstrong\u003Econnect directly to the sinoatrial node\u003C/strong\u003E. Instead, it transmits electrical impulses from the atrioventricular node to the ventricles. Its \u003Cstrong\u003Eintrinsic rhythm is actually 40-60 beats per minute\u003C/strong\u003E, not 60-80 as stated in one of the options. Finally, the bundle of His does not \u003Cstrong\u003Ereceive pacing signals from the atrioventricular node\u003C/strong\u003E. Under normal circumstances, it receives impulses from the atrioventricular node and conducts them to the ventricles, but it does not rely on the atrioventricular node for its pacing function.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The bundle of His can act as a pacemaker if the sinoatrial and atrioventricular nodes fail, with an intrinsic rate of 40-60 beats per minute.","The bundle of His is part of the cardiac conduction system, transmitting electrical impulses from the atrioventricular node to the ventricles."],"references":["Tortora, G. J., Derrickson, B., Burkett, B., Cooke, J., Di Pietro, F., Diversi, T., ... \u0026 Summers, S.. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 3rd Asia-Pacific Edition. 2022. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Karki R, Raina A, Ezzeddine FM, Bois MC, Asirvatham SJ. Anatomy and Pathology of the Cardiac Conduction System. Card Electrophysiol Clin. 2021 Dec;13(4):569-584. doi: 10.1016/j.ccep.2021.06.003. PMID: 34689887.","Padala SK, Cabrera JA, Ellenbogen KA. Anatomy of the cardiac conduction system. Pacing Clin Electrophysiol. 2021 Jan;44(1):15-25. doi: 10.1111/pace.14107. Epub 2020 Nov 12. PMID: 33118629."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"45660"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14432"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"45660","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/45660"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-10T13:01:35+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-10T13:02:56+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7127"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"60240"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"40","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/40"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\u2699\ufe0f","name":"Physiology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"4"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"41","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/41"},"attribut